<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,331,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Comments.</emphasis>
The examined material belongs to the 
<typeStatus box="[764,812,368,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1960" box="[917,1130,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi">
<emphasis box="[917,1130,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Zodarion lindbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the original description, Roewer considered this specimen as a subadult female. We can confirm that it is an adult female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1302,1408,403,430]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Parazodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raddei">
<emphasis box="[1302,1319,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1335,1408,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">raddei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species already reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[489,626,439,465]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(Pirzada, 
<collectingRegion box="[740,851,439,466]" country="Afghanistan" name="Kandahar" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Kandahar</collectingRegion>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Denis, J." box="[900,1051,439,466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" pagination="81 - 120" refId="ref6334" refString="Denis, J. (1958) Araignees (Araneidea) de l'Afghanistan. I. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening i KJObenhavn, 120, 81 - 120." type="journal article" year="1958">Denis (1958)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,331,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
Also, we noticed that in our previous paper (
<bibRefCitation author="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M." box="[711,999,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" pagination="145 - 193" refId="ref6801" refString="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M. (2021) Revision of the spider family Zodariidae (Arachnida, Araneae) in Iran and Turkmenistan, with seventeen new species. ZooKeys, 1035, 145 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1035.65767" type="journal article" year="2021">Zamani &amp; Marusik 2021</bibRefCitation>
), the figures 27A–D were erroneously attributed to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[298,400,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Parazodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raddei">
<emphasis box="[298,400,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">P. raddei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both the text and the caption. We hereby correct this error and attribute these images to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,773,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Acanthinozodium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elburzicum">
<emphasis box="[151,478,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Acanthinozodium elburzicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M." box="[486,773,547,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" pagination="145 - 193" refId="ref6801" refString="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M. (2021) Revision of the spider family Zodariidae (Arachnida, Araneae) in Iran and Turkmenistan, with seventeen new species. ZooKeys, 1035, 145 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1035.65767" type="journal article" year="2021">Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
